<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="86" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1779,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,555,1851,1876]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
Description (adult, male, n= 
<number box="[533,547,1851,1876]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" value="2.0">2</number>
)
</emphasis>
. Body length: 
<quantity box="[720,886,1851,1875]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" metricValueMax="5.2" metricValueMin="4.96" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="5.08" valueMax="5.2" valueMin="4.96">4.96–5.20 mm</quantity>
; pronotal length: 
<quantity box="[1081,1247,1851,1875]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.25" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="0.825" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.75">0.75–0.90 mm</quantity>
; greater pronotal width: 
<quantity box="[233,403,1887,1911]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.245" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.19" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="1.245" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.19">1.19–1.30 mm</quantity>
; elytral length 
<quantity box="[581,750,1887,1911]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.23" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="4.16" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="4.23" valueMax="4.3" valueMin="4.16">4.16–4.30 mm</quantity>
; elytral width 
<quantity box="[922,1091,1887,1911]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.275" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.25" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="1.275" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="1.25">1.25–1.30 mm</quantity>
. Integument overall brown to pale-yellow, including appendices, abdominal segments translucent from eight forward.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1779,2020]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,247]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="85" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,1960,1984]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Head</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[291,410,1959,1983]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStart-1="FIGURES 4 – 5" captionStart-2="FIGURES 6 – 8" captionStartId-0="3.[151,264,1823,1846]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionStartId-2="5.[151,264,1514,1537]" captionTargetBox-0="[174,1391,223,1780]" captionTargetBox-1="[200,1390,230,1909]" captionTargetBox-2="[187,1397,226,1452]" captionTargetId-0="figure@3.[151,1436,195,1830]" captionTargetId-1="figure@4.[179,1408,181,1935]" captionTargetId-2="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1493]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionTargetPageId-2="5" captionText-0="FIGURES 1 – 3. Memoan ciceroi gen. et sp. nov., holotype male from Estação Biológica Santa Lúcia, Santa Teresa, Espírito Santo, Brazil: 1, habitus dorsal; 2, habitus ventral; 3, head, frontal view, which shows the fusion of the fronto-clypeus and the labrum." captionText-1="FIGURES 4 – 5. Memoan ciceroi gen. nov. et sp. nov.: 4, head and thorax, ventral. Note the subcontiguous eyes and the conspicuous sutures between mesosternum and mesanepisternum, and between the mesanepisternum and mesanepimerum. 5, Mouthparts. Note the one-segmented labial palps." captionText-2="FIGURES 6 – 8. Memoan ciceroi gen. nov. et sp. nov.: 6, apical antennomeres. Note the fusion between the two apical-most antennomeres. 7, pronotum and elytral base, dorsal. Note the deep punctuation all along the pronotum, scutellum and elytra; and the pronotal parassagital, posterior elevations. 8, right wing." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/283658/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/283659/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/283660/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
FIGS 
<number box="[368,410,1959,1983]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6</number>
</figureCitation>
) Antennomeres densely and uniformly hairy. Scape nearly twice as long as pedicel, constrained on basal half, enlarging to apex. Pedicel as long as wide. Antennomere III longer than pedicel; III–IX laterally compressed, enlarging towards their apices; III–VI slightly decrease in length; VII–IX subequal in length to VI; X and XI connate; X + XI longer than IX. Maxillary palpomeres cylindrical, I–III transverse, I and III subequal and shorter than II; IV acuminate and membranous at apex, longer than the sum of II and III.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283661/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" targetBox="[201,1366,307,1828]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1877,1961]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,328,1877,1900]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">FIGURES 9–13.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[336,501,1879,1900]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Memoan" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ciceroi" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[336,501,1879,1900]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Memoan ciceroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[509,721,1878,1900]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[509,605,1878,1899]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[613,631,1879,1900]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">et</emphasis>
sp. nov.
</emphasis>
: 9, abdomen, left lateral; 10 abdomen, ventral (anterior end to left of page). 11, Detail of the abdomen, dorsal (arrows shows the dorsal spiracles); 12, aedeagal sheath: sintergite, dorsal and sternite IX, ventral (anterior ends to bottom of page). 13, aedeagus, dorsal.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,152,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">Thorax.</emphasis>
(FIGS 4,7) Anterior margin of pronotum with two feebly para-sagital sinuosities. Prosternum medially glabrous, with many lateral bristles. Meso-scutellum sub-pentagonal, with dense and deep punctures; lateral margins convergent posteriad, posterior margin emarginate; with sparse bristles in the anterior region of the punctures. Hypomeron with deep punctures, except for the central region. Mesosternum projecting and rounded posteriad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,331,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">Abdomen.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[338,465,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[201,1366,307,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[183,1410,269,1864]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 13. Memoan ciceroi gen. nov. et sp. nov.: 9, abdomen, left lateral; 10 abdomen, ventral (anterior end to left of page). 11, Detail of the abdomen, dorsal (arrows shows the dorsal spiracles); 12, aedeagal sheath: sintergite, dorsal and sternite IX, ventral (anterior ends to bottom of page). 13, aedeagus, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283661/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">
FIGS 
<number box="[407,465,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="86" value="11.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="9.0">9–13</number>
</figureCitation>
) Abdominal segments translucent from eight forward; lanterns occupying most of the venrite area. Pygidium with median lobe slightly acuminate, lateral lobes acute and projected. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">Terminalia and aedeagus:</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[291,439,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[201,1366,307,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[183,1410,269,1864]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 13. Memoan ciceroi gen. nov. et sp. nov.: 9, abdomen, left lateral; 10 abdomen, ventral (anterior end to left of page). 11, Detail of the abdomen, dorsal (arrows shows the dorsal spiracles); 12, aedeagal sheath: sintergite, dorsal and sternite IX, ventral (anterior ends to bottom of page). 13, aedeagus, dorsal." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/283661/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="86">
FIGS 
<number box="[368,439,404,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="86" value="12.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="12.0">12–13</number>
</figureCitation>
) sintergite half the sternite IX length, slightly asymmetrical; sternite IX narrowly prolonged anteriorly. Aedeagus almost entirely membranous. Phallobase symmetrical. Parameres basally constricted, with two thirds of phallus length. Apex of parameres and phallus rounded. Phallus slightly wider than a paramere. Ventral plate of phallus present, sides subparallel, slightly constrained medially.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
